---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { REPO_URL } from '../scripts/install-target'

const title = 'Privacy Policy — Dissatisfied'
const description =
	'We do not collect data today. If we do in the future, this policy will be updated first.'
const lastUpdated = 'December 25, 2025'
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} currentPath="/privacy">
	<article class="prose">
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

		<p>
			This Privacy Policy describes our policies and procedures on the
			collection, use, and disclosure of information when you use the Service
			and explains your privacy rights and how the law protects you. Right now,
			we do not collect Personal Data. If we introduce data collection in the
			future, we will update this policy first and clearly describe what is
			collected, why, and how it’s used.
		</p>
		<p>
			By using the Service, you agree to this Privacy Policy. This page was
			adapted from common templates to fit our product and our current stance:
			no data collection today; possible limited collection in future with prior
			notice.
		</p>

		<h2>Interpretation and Definitions</h2>
		<p>
			The words whose initial letters are capitalized have meanings defined
			under the following conditions.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Account</strong>: A unique account created for you to access our
				Service or parts of our Service (not used today).
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Affiliate</strong>: An entity that controls, is controlled by,
				or is under common control with us.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Application</strong>: Dissatisfied, the browser extension we
				provide.
			</li>
			<li><strong>Company</strong>: Dissatisfied (“we”, “us”, or “our”).</li>
			<li><strong>Country</strong>: California, United States.</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Device</strong>: Any device that can access the Service, such as
				a computer or phone.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Personal Data</strong>: Information that relates to an
				identified or identifiable individual.
			</li>
			<li><strong>Service</strong>: The Application (and this website).</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Service Provider</strong>: Third parties that might process data
				on our behalf (none used today).
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Usage Data</strong>: Data generated by using the Service or from
				the Service infrastructure.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>You</strong>: The individual accessing or using the Service, or
				the organization you represent.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Collecting and Using Your Personal Data</h2>
		<p>
			<strong>Current stance:</strong> We do not collect Personal Data today.
		</p>
		<h3>Types of Data Collected</h3>
		<p><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Not collected.</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Usage Data:</strong> Not collected by the extension today. If, in the
			future, we introduce limited telemetry (e.g., basic diagnostics), details will
			be documented here before any collection begins.
		</p>

		<h2>Use of Your Personal Data</h2>
		<p>
			Since we do not collect data today, the purposes below are only applicable
			if data collection is introduced in the future:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Provide and maintain the Service, including monitoring usage.</li>
			<li>Manage Account features (if accounts are ever introduced).</li>
			<li>Perform contracts (e.g., purchases) if commerce is added.</li>
			<li>
				Contact you for updates or support (with your consent or where lawful).
			</li>
			<li>Provide news and offers (opt-in only).</li>
			<li>Handle requests you send us.</li>
			<li>
				Evaluate business transfers (e.g., mergers) where Personal Data could be
				among transferred assets.
			</li>
			<li>Analyze usage trends to improve the Service.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Sharing Your Personal Data</h2>
		<p>
			We do not sell Personal Data. If future collection is introduced, sharing
			could occur in limited cases:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>With service providers to support or analyze the Service.</li>
			<li>During business transfers (e.g., mergers or acquisitions).</li>
			<li>With affiliates that must honor this policy.</li>
			<li>With business partners to offer features (opt-in).</li>
			<li>With other users if you choose to make information public.</li>
			<li>With your consent.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Retention</h2>
		<p>
			No data is retained today because none is collected. If data collection
			begins, retention periods will reflect legal requirements, security needs,
			and the purpose of processing.
		</p>

		<h2>Transfer of Your Personal Data</h2>
		<p>
			We do not transfer Personal Data today. If future collection begins, data
			could be processed in locations outside your jurisdiction. We would only
			transfer data where adequate protections are in place.
		</p>

		<h2>Delete Your Personal Data</h2>
		<p>
			Not applicable today. If data collection is introduced, you will have
			rights to delete or request deletion of Personal Data subject to legal
			obligations.
		</p>

		<h2>Disclosure</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Business Transactions:</strong> If involved in a merger or sale, Personal
				Data (if any) may be transferred with prior notice.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Law Enforcement & Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose data
				when required by law or to protect rights, safety, and prevent abuse.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Security</h2>
		<p>
			We strive to use reasonable measures to protect information. No method is
			100% secure.
		</p>

		<h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
		<p>
			The Service is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly
			collect information from them.
		</p>

		<h2>Links to Other Websites</h2>
		<p>External sites may have their own policies; review them before use.</p>

		<h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
		<p>
			We may update this policy. We will post changes here and update the “Last
			updated” date.
		</p>

		<h2>Contact Us</h2>
		<p>
			Questions? Visit
			<a href={REPO_URL} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">our GitHub</a>.
		</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
